      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly, here's a basic Python function using `spacy`, which should meet your requirements:\n\n```python\nimport spacy\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n\ndef parse_dependencies(sentence):\n    doc = nlp(sentence)\n    dependencies = []\n    for token in doc:\n        # Get the head and the child word (dep) of each token\n        head = token.head.text\n        child = token.text\n        # If the child word is not empty, we add the relationship to the results\n        if child:\n            dependencies.append((head, child))\n    return dependencies\n\n# Test the function\nsentence = \"the patient shows signs of acute respiratory distress\"\nexpected_deps = [\n    (\"shows\", \"patient\"),\n    (\"shows\", \"signs\"),\n    (\"signs\", \"of\"),\n    (\"of\", \"distress\"),\n    (\"distress\", \"respiratory\"),\n    (\"respiratory\", \"acute\")\n]\n\nprint(parse_dependencies(sentence))\n```\n\nEnsure you have `spacy` and the English model installed. You can install them using pip if needed:\n\n```bash\npip install spacy\npython -m spacy download en_core_web_sm\n```\n\nThe function will return the",
